I had overestimated my forces. A serious relapse hospitalized me fornearly a whole year. The complete rest ordered by all my doctors was thenbotched by my having to stand by my publisher in a long legal fight againstobscenity charges leveled at my novel by stuffy censors. I was again veryill. I still feel the pressure of the hallucinations that beset me, as mysearch for Bel got somehow mixed up with the controversy over my novel, 